history.content: Usually lab space is just more limited. So a lab will only have a specific number of workstations and is capped at a smaller number of students, while discussion sections can be in a classroom and can accommodate more. The discussion sections may be placed at higher caps to allow students to have flexibility in their discussion sections. For example, if there are 2 labs each capped at 20 and 2 discussions each capped at 30, then maybe 25 students would pick discussion 1 because it fits better with their schedule. There is no point in unnecessarily preventing students from registering for more convenient discussions if there is no need to do so. This is why the lecture seats/discussion seats/lab seats may not always add up.

children.subject: It's possible that they only have enough GSIs to schedule a certain number of labs, yes. Usually lecture size is just the max number of people that can fit in the lecture hall. It's also possible that more labs won't be added though.
